<p>
<seg id=1> US and North Korea decided to continue their talks on Friday about investigating a suspected underground nuclear base near Pyongyang. </seg>
<seg id=2> Representatives from two sides will hold a meeting in New York for two days and then continue their talks in Washington. </seg>
<seg id=3> The two sides had similar talks last month in Pyongyang. </seg>
<seg id=4> The talks were announced to be broken because of a demand raised by the North Korea. </seg>
<seg id=5> North Korea asked the US to provide 3000 million US dollars as an exchange for the North Korea to allow the investigators to enter all the related places. </seg>
<seg id=6> Before holding the new talks, North Korea had a series of attacks toward US. </seg>
</p>
